in Telamon used the One Power to destroy himself, creating a massive mountain."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A small village in the Two Rivers, located near several rivers and far from major cities, with a history extending back for over a thousand years."},{"name":"The Inn of the Emond's Field","description":"A central location where travelers stay and local residents gather, especially during festivals."},{"name":"The Wagon Bridge","description":"A bridge in Emond's Field that recently had a crowd gathered around it, escorting a peddler's wagon towards it."},{"name":"Winefly Inn","description":"A historic inn in Emond's Field, possibly the oldest building in the area, mentioned as an important meeting place."}],"summary":"Rand and his friends Mat and Ewin encounter a mysterious woman named Moiraine who gives them silver pennies and seeks their help with historical research in Emond's Field. Meanwhile, the long-awaited peddler arrives, setting the stage for the upcoming Bel Tine festival."}},{"index":40,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Robert Jordan","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Cover Page","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the book series.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"The cover page contains quotes about his work."},{"name":"Lews Therin Telamon","aliases":["Dragon"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeler who is blamed for the Breaking of the World.","relationships":[{"character":"Ilyena Sunhair","relationship":" Wife who was killed by his hand"},{"character":"Betrayer of the Nation","relationship":"Enemy who tempted him to use saidin"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to an isolated place and used the One Power to destroy himself and his body, creating a massive mountain."},{"name":"Ilyena Sunhair","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentL