 mountain."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A village located not far from Ghealdan and bordering the Forest of Emond, where the people of the Two Rivers reside."},{"name":"The Inn of the Emond's Field","description":"A central location where travelers stay and local residents gather, especially during festivals."},{"name":"The Wagon Bridge","description":"A bridge in Emond's Field that recently had a crowd gathered around it, escorting a peddler's wagon towards it."},{"name":"Winefly Inn","description":"A historic inn in Emond's Field, possibly the oldest building in the area, mentioned as an important meeting place."},{"name":"Taren Ferry","description":"A village located north of the Taren river mentioned as having strange customs and a habit of electing Wisdoms from outside."},{"name":"Forest of Emond","description":"A vast wood surrounding Emond's Field, where the mysterious rider is believed to be hiding."},{"name":"The Quarry Road","description":"A road connecting Emond's Field with nearby quarries, along which Rand and Tam travel."}],"summary":"Rand fights off a Trolloc that attacked his severely wounded father, Tam. After retrieving supplies and necessities, Rand plans to move Tam to Emond's Field for Nynaeve's medical attention."}},{"index":43,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Robert Jordan","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Cover Page","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the book series.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"The cover page contains quotes about his work."},{"name":"Lews Therin Telamon","aliases":["Dragon"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeler who is blamed for the Breaking of the World.","relationships":[{"character":"Ilyena Sunhair","relationship":" Wife who was killed by his hand"},{"character":"Betrayer of the Nation","relationship":"Enemy who tempted him to use saidin"}],"recentEv