roviding care"}],"recentEvents":"Suffered from a fever that was treated by Nynaeve and Rand."},{"name":"Mistress Luhhan","aliases":["Master Luhhan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"this chapter","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The blacksmith who has been Rand's mentor in smithing and is known for his strong and sturdy hammer.","relationships":[{"character":"Perrin Aybara","relationship":"apprentice"},{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a hammer search based on Perrin's encounter with a strange rider."},{"name":"Haral Luhhan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A strong and brave blacksmith, who has a fear of blood and butchering scenes.","relationships":[{"character":"Bran al'Vere","relationship":"Village Council Member"}],"recentEvents":"Haral mentions Perrin's sighting of the strange rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Padan Fain","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Wolf Hunt","currentLocation":"Near Emond's Field","description":"A mysterious figure suspected of traveling near Emond's Field, stirring fears among the villagers.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Unfamiliar Stranger"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Unfamiliar Stranger"}],"recentEvents":"Fain is discussed by the Village Council, who is unsure whether he poses a real danger."},{"name":"Jon Thane","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A village resident, father of Lem, who saw the mysterious rider.","relationships":[{"character":"Lem Thane","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Jon reports his son's sighting of the mysterious rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Samel Crawe","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A resident of Emond's Field, father of Bandry, who reports his son's sighting of the strange rider.","relationships":[{"character":"Bandry Crawe","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Samel reports his son Bandry's sighting of the mysterious rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Lan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Journey","currentLocation":"The village","description":"A silent and grim-faced Warder of Moiraine, very protective of her despite her dismissals.","relationships":[{"character":"Moiraine","relationship":"Warder"},{"character":"Rand","relationship":"Disapproved of Rand's pushy behavior towards Moiraine"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Rand that Moiraine is exhausted after a night's battle."}],"locations":[{"name":"Isolated Plain","description":"A flat and empty land where Lews Therin Telamon used the One Power to destroy himself, creating a massive mountain."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A small village in the Westlands, preparing for Winternight festivities."},{"name":"The Inn of the Emond's Field","description":"A central location where travelers stay and local residents gather, especially during festivals."},{"name":"The Wagon Bridge","description":"A bridge in Emond's Field that recently had a crowd gathered around it, escorting a peddler's wagon towards it."},{"name":"Winefly Inn","description":"A historic inn in Emond's Field, possibly the oldest building in the area, mentioned as an important meeting place."},{"name":"Taren Ferry","description":"A village located north of the Taren river mentioned as having strange customs and a habit of electing Wisdoms from outside."},{"name":"Forest of Emond","description":"A vast wood surrounding Emond's Field, where the mysterious rider is believed to be hiding."},{"name":"The Quarry Road","description":"A road connecting Emond's Field with nearby quarries, along which Rand and Tam travel."},{"name":"The village","description":"A place currently dealing with the aftermath of a Trolloc attack, where bonfires burn to dispose of the bodies with a foul stench."}],"summary":"Rand seeks help from Moiraine, an Aes Sedai, to heal his father after the Wisdom refuses to help. Moiraine, with her Warder Lan, agrees to assist despite the concerns and stigma surrounding Aes Sedai."}},{"index":45,"result":{"characters":[{"name":"Robert Jordan","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Cover Page","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The author of the book series.","relationships":[],"recentEvents":"The cover page contains quotes about his work."},{"name":"Lews Therin Telamon","aliases":["Dragon"],"importance":"main","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeler who is blamed for the Breaking of the World.","relationships":[{"character":"Ilyena Sunhair","relationship":" Wife who was killed by his hand"},{"character":"Betrayer of the Nation","relationship":"Enemy who tempted him to use saidin"}],"recentEvents":"Traveled to an isolated place and used the One Power to destroy himself and his body, creating a massive mountain."},{"name":"Ilyena Sunhair","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"dead","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"The wife of Lews Therin Telamon.","relationships":[{"character":"Lews Therin Telamon","relationship":"Wife killed by her husband's action"}],"recentEvents":"Was remembered by Lews Therin as he destroyed himself to cleanse saidin."},{"name":"Betrayer of the Nation","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Breaking of the World","currentLocation":"Unknown","description":"A powerful channeler who tempted Lews Therin to use saidin.","relationships":[{"character":"Lews Therin Telamon","relationship":"Enemy who caused the Breaking of the World"}],"recentEvents":"Confronted Lews Therin and reminded him of his sins and the destruction of the world."},{"name":"Rand al'Thor","aliases":["Rand","Shepherd of the Night"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Borderlands","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man from Emond's Field believed to be the Dragon Reborn.","relationships":[{"character":"Moiraine Sedai","relationship":"Trusted but mysterious guide"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Father"},{"character":"Mayor Abell Cauthon","relationship":"Mayor of Emond's Field"},{"character":"Nynaeve al'Meara","relationship":"Acquaintance"},{"character":"Mistress al'Vere","relationship":"Neighbor and caretaker"}],"recentEvents":"Faced with the reality of the Trollocs' true intentions, Rand was convinced to follow Moiraine's advice for the safety of Emond's Field."},{"name":"Mat Cauthon","aliases":["Mat"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tragedy","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young man known for his luck and penchant for causing trouble, Mat has a reputation as a thief and trickster.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Perrin Aybara","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Saw a mysterious man on horseback and told Rand and Perrin about it."},{"name":"Bran al'Vere","aliases":["Mayor of Emond's Field"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The mayor of Emond's Field, who acts as the Village Council leader and decision-maker during emergencies.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Village Resident"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Village Resident"},{"character":"Haral Luhhan","relationship":"Village Blacksmith"}],"recentEvents":"Bran meets with the Village Council to address the worries over Aes Sedai and the false Dragon."},{"name":"Tam al'Thor","aliases":["Father"],"importance":"main","status":"unknown","lastSeen":"A Village in the Borderlands","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"Rand's father, an enigmatic man who has shared past and present secrets.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Son"},{"character":"Moiraine Sedai","relationship":"Stranger who appeared after his return to Emond's Field"}],"recentEvents":"Tam is recovering from injuries sustained when the village was attacked by the Trollocs, now in a coma-like state."},{"name":"Cenn Buie","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"An elderly member of the Village Council who sometimes disagrees with others’ decisions.","relationships":[{"character":"Bran al'Vere","relationship":"Village Council Member"}],"recentEvents":"Cenn disbelieves the young men's testimony about the mystery rider."},{"name":"Matrim Cauthon","aliases":["Mat","The ta'veren"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A youth from Emond's Field with a quick wit and a propensity for gambling; a close friend of Rand and Perrin.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Close male friend"},{"character":"Perrin Aybar","relationship":"Close male friend"},{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"Female friend"}],"recentEvents":"Refused the silver penny given to him by a woman called Moiraine and worried about meeting a mysterious man named Lan."},{"name":"Ewin Abendroth","aliases":["Ewin"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Village of Emond's Field","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young boy in Emond's Field, a friend of Rand and Mat.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Friend"},{"character":"Matrim Cauthon","relationship":"Friend"}],"recentEvents":"Received a silver penny from a woman named Moiraine."},{"name":"Moiraine Damodred","aliases":["Moiraine Sedai","Aes Sedai"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Borderlands","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"An Aes Sedai who has taken a special interest in Rand.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Guide and mentor"},{"character":"Lan Mandragoran","relationship":"Guardian and Warder"}],"recentEvents":"Convinced Rand and Tam that the Trollocs were after them and not random destruction, convincing them that leaving Emond's Field is the safest option."},{"name":"Lan Mandragoran","aliases":["Lan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Borderlands","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A Warder and protector for Moiraine, skilled in combat and loyal.","relationships":[{"character":"Moiraine Sedai","relationship":"Aes Sedai and Warden"},{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Guardian and mentor, alongside Moiraine"}],"recentEvents":"Fighting alongside Moiraine against the Trolloc attack."},{"name":"Egwene al'Vere","aliases":["Egwene"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tragedy","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young girl who dreams of leading her village as Wisdom and learning to understand the wind.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Nynaeve al'Meara","relationship":"trainer"}],"recentEvents":"Talked with Rand about marriage and her desire to be a Wisdom, and dismissed his and the others' claims of seeing a black-cloaked rider."},{"name":"Perrin Aybara","aliases":["Perrin"],"importance":"main","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tragedy","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A strong and kind blacksmith’s son, known for his sense of duty and loyalty to his friends.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"},{"character":"Mat Cauthon","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Saw a strange rider near the village and discussed the encounter with Rand and Mat."},{"name":"Nynaeve al'Meara","aliases":["Nynaeve"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Tragedy","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A young woman who has aspirations to be the Wisdom and possesses a strong sense of duty and compassion.","relationships":[{"character":"Egwene al'Vere","relationship":"trainer"},{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"villager"}],"recentEvents":"Saw the mysterious man in black and discussed his sighting with Rand, Mat, and Perrin."},{"name":"Mistress Ayellin","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"this chapter","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"An older woman who was suffering from a fever that Rand and the Wisdom helped to treat.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"patient"},{"character":"Nynaeve al'Meara","relationship":"Wisdom providing care"}],"recentEvents":"Suffered from a fever that was treated by Nynaeve and Rand."},{"name":"Mistress Luhhan","aliases":["Master Luhhan"],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"this chapter","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"The blacksmith who has been Rand's mentor in smithing and is known for his strong and sturdy hammer.","relationships":[{"character":"Perrin Aybara","relationship":"apprentice"},{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"friend"}],"recentEvents":"Conducted a hammer search based on Perrin's encounter with a strange rider."},{"name":"Haral Luhhan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A strong and brave blacksmith, who has a fear of blood and butchering scenes.","relationships":[{"character":"Bran al'Vere","relationship":"Village Council Member"}],"recentEvents":"Haral mentions Perrin's sighting of the strange rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Padan Fain","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"The Wolf Hunt","currentLocation":"Near Emond's Field","description":"A mysterious figure suspected of traveling near Emond's Field, stirring fears among the villagers.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Unfamiliar Stranger"},{"character":"Tam al'Thor","relationship":"Unfamiliar Stranger"}],"recentEvents":"Fain is discussed by the Village Council, who is unsure whether he poses a real danger."},{"name":"Jon Thane","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A village resident, father of Lem, who saw the mysterious rider.","relationships":[{"character":"Lem Thane","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Jon reports his son's sighting of the mysterious rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Samel Crawe","aliases":[],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"Balefire","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A resident of Emond's Field, father of Bandry, who reports his son's sighting of the strange rider.","relationships":[{"character":"Bandry Crawe","relationship":"Son"}],"recentEvents":"Samel reports his son Bandry's sighting of the mysterious rider to the Village Council."},{"name":"Lan","aliases":[],"importance":"secondary","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A New Journey","currentLocation":"The village","description":"A silent and grim-faced Warder of Moiraine, very protective of her despite her dismissals.","relationships":[{"character":"Moiraine","relationship":"Warder"},{"character":"Rand","relationship":"Disapproved of Rand's pushy behavior towards Moiraine"}],"recentEvents":"Warned Rand that Moiraine is exhausted after a night's battle."},{"name":"Mistress al'Vere","aliases":["Merrilin"],"importance":"minor","status":"alive","lastSeen":"A Village in the Borderlands","currentLocation":"Emond's Field","description":"A caring woman who takes care of the injured and concerned citizens of Emond's Field.","relationships":[{"character":"Rand al'Thor","relationship":"Neighbor and current caretaker"},{"character":"Mayor Abell Cauthon","relationship":"Husband and Mayor's wife"}],"recentEvents":"Providing care for Tam and ensuring Rand gets enough rest, worried about the impact of the Trolloc attack on the village."}],"locations":[{"name":"Isolated Plain","description":"A flat and empty land where Lews Therin Telamon used the One Power to destroy himself, creating a massive mountain."},{"name":"Emond's Field","description":"A peaceful village in the Two Rivers, now under threat from Trolloc attacks."},{"name":"The Inn of the Emond's Field","description":"A central location where travelers stay and local residents gather, especially during festivals."},{"name":"The Wagon Bridge","description":"A bridge in Emond's Field that recently had a crowd gathered around it, escorting a peddler's wagon towards it."},{"name":"Winefly Inn","description":"A historic inn in Emond's Field, possibly the oldest building in the area, mentioned as an important meeting place."},{"name":"Taren Ferry","description":"A village located north of the Taren river mentioned as having strange customs and a habit of electing Wisdoms from outside."},{"name":"Forest of Emond","description":"A vast wood surrounding Emond's Field, where the mysterious rider is believed to be hiding."},{"name":"The Quarry Road","description":"A road connecting Emond's Field with nearby quarries, along which Rand and Tam travel."},{"name":"The village","description":"A place currently dealing with the aftermath of a Trolloc attack, where bonfires burn to dispose of the bodies with a foul stench."}],"summary":"Rand learns from Moiraine that the Trolloc attack was aimed at him and his father, Tam, making their departure crucial for the village's safety. Tam remains in a deep coma-like state, and the village is still reeling from the reality of the supernatural threats."}}]},"mapState":null}